===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{liushu|p}} or {{Han compound|𠘧|又|ls=ic|t1=|t2=|no_och2=1}} – a hand holding a tool similar to a hammer, hence activity (with a reference to the act of "beating"). See also [[段]] and the original version on oracle bones of [[鼓]].

The whole character was then borrowed phonetically to indicate an ancient halberd made of bamboo.

